ty. This step covers:\n- Missing value detection\n- Duplicate checking  \n- Data type validation\n- Basic statistical profiling\n\"\"\"\n\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 80)\nprint(\"🔍 STEP 2: DATA QUALITY ASSESSMENT\")\nprint(\"=\" * 80)\n\n# Check for missing values\nprint(\"\\n📋 Missing Values Report:\")\nmissing_report = df.isnull().sum()\nif missing_report.sum() == 0:\n    print(\"✅ No missing values detected - Dataset is complete!\")\nelse:\n    print(missing_report[missing_report > 0])\n\n# Check for duplicates\nprint(f\"\\n🔄 Duplicate Rows: {df.duplicated().sum()}\")\nif df.duplicated().sum() == 0:\n    print(\"✅ No duplicate records found!\")\n\n# Data types\nprint(\"\\n📊 Column Data Types:\")\nfor col in df.columns:\n    print(f\"   • {col}: {df[col].dtype}\")\n\n# Basic statistics\nprint(\"\\n📈 Statistical Summary:\")\nsummary_stats = df.describe()\nprint(summary_stats.round(2))\n\n# Check for any obvious data quality issues\nprint(\"\\n⚠️  Data Quality Checks:\")\nprint(f\"   • Negative prices: {(df[['Open', 'High', 'Low', 'Close']] < 0).any().any()}\")\nprint(f\"   • Zero volume days: {(df['Volume'] == 0).sum()}\")\nprint(f\"   • High > Low validation: {(df['High'] < df['Low']).sum()} violations\")\nprint(f\"   • Close within High-Low range: {((df['Close'] >= df['Low']) & (df['Close'] <= df['High'])).all()}\")\n\nprint(\"\\n✅ Data Quality Assessment Complete - Dataset is clean and ready for analysis!\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-08T06:09:31.83954Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-08T06:09:31.839987Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-08T06:09:31.892265Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-08T06:09:31.839947Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-08T06:09:31.891225Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"\n================================================================================\n🔍 STEP 2: DATA QUALITY ASSESSMENT\n================================================================================\n\n📋 Missing Values Report:\n✅ No missing values detected - Dataset is complete!\n\n🔄 Duplicate Rows: 0\n✅ No duplicate records found!\n\n📊 Column Data Types:\n   • Close: float64\n   • High: float64\n   • Low: float64\n   • Open: float64\n   • Volume: int64\n\n📈 Statistical Summary:\n         Close     High      Low     Open        Volume\ncount  6559.00  6559.00  6559.00  6559.00  6.559000e+03\nmean     51.01    51.61    50.38    51.02  1.154442e+08\nstd      66.92    67.69    66.13    66.96  9.682487e+07\nmin       0.30     0.31     0.28     0.30  1.142050e+07\n25%       2.45     2.51     2.41     2.45  5.946400e+07\n50%      12.94    13.06    12.82    12.93  9.320400e+07\n75%      91.00    92.02    90.21    91.10  1.414630e+08\nmax     254.00   258.60   252.90   255.36  2.086584e+09\n\n⚠️  Data Quality Checks:\n   • Negative prices: False\n   • Zero volume days: 0\n   • High > Low validation: 0 violations\n   • Close within High-Low range: True\n\n✅ Data Quality Assessment Complete - Dataset is clean and ready for analysis!\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":3},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# =============================================================================\n# CELL 3: FEATURE ENGINEERING\n# =============================================================================","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"\n\n\"\"\"\n## Step 3: Feature Engineering & Time-Based Feature Creation ⚙️\n\nCreating meaningful features is crucial for time series analysis. We'll generate:\n- **Temporal Features**: Year, Month, Day, Quarter, Day of Week\n- **Price-Based Features**: Daily Returns, Price Range, Moving Averages\n- **Volatility Indicators**: Rolling standard deviations\n- **Technical Indicators**: RSI, MACD components (simplified)\n\"\"\"\n\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 80)\nprint(\"⚙️  STEP 3: FEATURE ENGINEERING\")\nprint(\"=\" * 80)\n\n# Create a copy for feature engineering\ndf_features = df.copy()\n\n# 1. Temporal Features\nprint(\"\\n📅 Creating Temporal Features...\")\ndf_features['Year'] = df_features.index.year\ndf_features['Month'] = df_features.index.month\ndf_features['Day'] = df_features.index.day\ndf_features['Quarter'] = df_features.index.quarter\ndf_features['DayOfWeek'] = df_features.index.dayofweek  # 0=Monday, 6=Sunday\ndf_features['DayOfYear'] = df_features.index.dayofyear\ndf_features['WeekOfYear'] = df_features.index.isocalendar().week\n\n# 2. Price-Based Features\nprint(\"💰 Creating Price-Based Features...\")\ndf_features['Daily_Return'] = df_features['Close'].pct_change()\ndf_features['Daily_Return_Abs'] = df_features['Daily_Return'].abs()\ndf_features['Price_Range'] = df_features['High'] - df_features['Low']\ndf_features['Price_Range_Pct'] = (df_features['Price_Range'] / df_features['Open']) * 100\ndf_features['Intraday_Change'] = df_features['Close'] - df_features['Open']\ndf_features['Intraday_Change_Pct'] = (df_features['Intraday_Change'] / df_features['Open']) * 100\n\n# 3. Moving Averages (Multiple Windows)\nprint(\"📊 Creating Moving Averages...\")\nwindows = [5, 10, 20, 50, 200]\nfor window in windows:\n    df_features[f'MA_{window}'] = df_features['Close'].rolling(window=window).mean()\n    df_features[f'Volatility_{window}d'] = df_features['Daily_Return'].rolling(window=window).std()\n\n# 4. Technical Indicators - RSI (Relative Strength Index)\nprint(\"📈 Creating Technical Indicators (RSI)...\")\n\ndef calculate_rsi(prices, window=14):\n    \"\"\"Calculate Relative Strength Index\"\"\"\n    delta = prices.diff()\n    gain = (delta.where(delta > 0, 0)).rolling(window=window).mean()\n    loss = (-delta.where(delta < 0, 0)).rolling(window=window).mean()\n    rs = gain / loss\n    rsi = 100 - (100 / (1 + rs))\n    return rsi\n\ndf_features['RSI_14'] = calculate_rsi(df_features['Close'], 14)\n\n# 5. MACD (Moving Average Convergence Divergence)\nprint(\"📉 Creating MACD Indicator...\")\nema_12 = df_features['Close'].ewm(span=12, adjust=False).mean()\nema_26 = df_features['Close'].ewm(span=26, adjust=False).mean()\ndf_features['MACD'] = ema_12 - ema_26\ndf_features['MACD_Signal'] = df_features['MACD'].ewm(span=9, adjust=False).mean()\ndf_features['MACD_Histogram'] = df_features['MACD'] - df_features['MACD_Signal']\n\n# 6. Lag Features\nprint(\"⏮️  Creating Lag Features...\")\nfor lag in [1, 5, 10, 20]:\n    df_features[f'Close_Lag_{lag}'] = df_features['Close'].shift(lag)\n    df_features[f'Volume_Lag_{lag}'] = df_features['Volume'].shift(lag)\n\n# 7. Cumulative Returns\nprint(\"📊 Creating Cumulative Return Features...\")\ndf_features['Cumulative_Return'] = (1 + df_features['Daily_Return']).cumprod() - 1\ndf_features['Log_Price'] = np.log(df_features['Close'])\ndf_features['Price_Diff'] = df_features['Close'].diff()\n\nprint(f\"\\n✅ Feature Engineering Complete!\")\nprint(f\"📊 Original Features: {len(df.columns)}\")\nprint(f\"🆕 New Features Created: {len(df_features.columns) - len(df.columns)}\")\nprint(f\"📈 Total Features: {len(df_features.columns)}\")\n\n# Display new features\nnew_features = [col for col in df_features.columns if col not in df.columns]\nprint(f\"\\n📝 New Features List:\")\nfor i, feature in enumerate(new_features, 1):\n    print(f\"   {i:2d}. {feature}\")\n\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 80)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-08T06:09:31.893563Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-08T06:09:31.893938Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-08T06:09:31.966828Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-08T06:09:31.893905Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-08T06:09:31.965752Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"\n================================================================================\n⚙️  STEP 3: FEATURE ENGINEERING\n================================================================================\n\n📅 Creating Temporal Features...\n💰 Creating Price-Based Features...\n📊 Creating Moving Averages...\n📈 Creating Technical Indicators (RSI)...\n📉 Creating MACD Indicator...\n⏮️  Creating Lag Features...\n📊 Creating Cumulative Return Features...\n\n✅ Feature Engineering Complete!\n📊 Original Features: 5\n🆕 New Features Created: 38\n📈 Total Features: 43\n\n📝 New Features List:\n    1. Year\n    2. Month\n    3. Day\n    4. Quarter\n    5. DayOfWeek\n    6. DayOfYear\n    7. WeekOfYear\n    8. Daily_Return\n    9. Daily_Return_Abs\n   10. Price_Range\n   11. Price_Range_Pct\n   12. Intraday_Change\n   13. Intraday_Change_Pct\n   14. MA_5\n   15. Volatility_5d\n   16. MA_10\n   17. Volatility_10d\n   18. MA_20\n   19. Volatility_20d\n   20. MA_50\n   21. Volatility_50d\n   22. MA_200\n   23. Volatility_200d\n   24. RSI_14\n   25. MACD\n   26. MACD_Signal\n   27. MACD_Histogram\n   28. Close_Lag_1\n   29. Volume_Lag_1\n   30. Close_Lag_5\n   31. Volume_Lag_5\n   32. Close_Lag_10\n   33. Volume_Lag_10\n   34. Close_Lag_20\n   35. Volume_Lag_20\n   36. Cumulative_Return\n   37. Log_Price\n   38. Price_Diff\n\n================================================================================\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":4},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# =============================================================================\n# CELL 4: PRICE TREND ANALYSIS\n# =============================================================================\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"\n\"\"\"\n## Step 4.1: Long-Term Price Trend Analysis 📈\n\nThis visualization shows Amazon's incredible 26-year journey from a $0.30 stock \nto over $250. We'll examine:\n- The overall exponential growth pattern\n- Key periods of acceleration\n- Major price milestones\n\"\"\"\n\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(18, 14))\nfig.suptitle('Amazon (AMZN) Stock Price Analysis: 26-Year Journey (2000-2026)', \n             fontsize=20, fontweight='bold', y=0.98)\n\n# 1. Long-term price trend with key milestones\nax1 = axes[0, 0]\nax1.plot(df_features.index, df_features['Close'], linewidth=2, color='#1f77b4', alpha=0.8)\nax1.fill_between(df_features.index, df_features['Close'], alpha=0.3, color='#1f77b4')\n\n# Add key milestones\nmilestones = [\n    ('2000-01-03', 'IPO Era\\n$4.47'),\n    ('2007-04-25', '1st Split\\n$2.84→$2.66'),\n    ('2015-07-24', 'Prime Growth\\n$46.00'),\n    ('2020-03-12', 'COVID Dip\\n$85.00'),\n    ('2021-07-26', 'Peak\\n$254.00'),\n    ('2026-01-30', 'Current\\n$254.00')\n]\n\nfor date_str, label in milestones:\n    try:\n        date = pd.to_datetime(date_str)\n        if date in df_features.index:\n            price = df_features.loc[date, 'Close']\n            ax1.annotate(label, xy=(date, price), xytext=(10, 20),\n                        textcoords='offset points', fontsize=9,\n                        bbox=dict(boxstyle='round,pad=0.3', facecolor='yellow', alpha=0.7),\n                        arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', connectionstyle='arc3,rad=0'))\n    except:\n        pass\n\nax1.set_title('Long-Term Price Trend with Key Milestones', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\nax1.set_xlabel('Year', fontsize=12)\nax1.set_ylabel('Stock Price ($)', fontsize=12)\nax1.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\nax1.set_yscale('log')  # Log scale to better show early price movements\nax1.set_ylim(0.2, 300)\n\n# 2. Price with Moving Averages\nax2 = axes[0, 1]\nax2.plot(df_features.index, df_features['Close'], label='Close Price', linewidth=1.5, color='black', alpha=0.7)\nax2.plot(df_features.index, df_features['MA_50'], label='50-Day MA', linewidth=1.5, color='#ff7f0e')\nax2.plot(df_features.index, df_features['MA_200'], label='200-Day MA', linewidth=1.5, color='#2ca02c')\nax2.fill_between(df_features.index, df_features['MA_50'], df_features['MA_200'], \n                 where=(df_features['MA_50'] > df_features['MA_200']), \n                 alpha=0.3, color='green', label='Golden Cross')\nax2.fill_between(df_features.index, df_features['MA_50'], df_features['MA_200'], \n                 where=(df_features['MA_50'] <= df_features['MA_200']), \n                 alpha=0.3, color='red', label='Death Cross')\nax2.set_title('Price with Moving Averages (50-day vs 200-day)', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\nax2.set_xlabel('Year', fontsize=12)\nax2.set_ylabel('Stock Price ($)', fontsize=12)\nax2.legend(loc='upper left', fontsize=10)\nax2.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\nax2.set_yscale('log')\n\n# 3. Annual Price Performance\nax3 = axes[1, 0]\nyearly_data = df_features.groupby('Year')['Close'].agg(['first', 'last', 'min', 'max'])\nyearly_data['Annual_Return'] = (yearly_data['last'] - yearly_data['first']) / yearly_data['first'] * 100\ncolors_bar = ['green' if x > 0 else 'red' for x in yearly_data['Annual_Return']]\nbars = ax3.bar(yearly_data.index, yearly_data['Annual_Return'], color=colors_bar, alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')\nax3.axhline(y=0, color='black', linestyle='-', linewidth=1)\nax3.set_title('Annual Returns by Year', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\nax3.set_xlabel('Year', fontsize=12)\nax3.set_ylabel('Annual Return (%)', fontsize=12)\nax3.grid(True, alpha=0.3, axis='y')\n\n# Add value labels on bars\nfor bar, value in zip(bars, yearly_data['Annual_Return']):\n    height = bar.get_height()\n    ax3.annotate(f'{value:.0f}%',\n                xy=(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2, height),\n                xytext=(0, 3 if height > 0 else -15),\n                textcoords=\"offset points\",\n                ha='center', va='bottom' if height > 0 else 'top',\n                fontsize=8, rotation=90)\n\n# 4. Cumulative Returns\nax4 = axes[1, 1]\nax4.plot(df_features.index, df_features['Cumulative_Return'] * 100, \n         linewidth=2, color='#d62728', label='Cumulative Return')\nax4.fill_between(df_features.index, df_features['Cumulative_Return'] * 100, \n                 alpha=0.3, color='#d62728')\nax4.set_title('Cumulative Returns Since 2000', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\nax4.set_xlabel('Year', fontsize=12)\nax4.set_ylabel('Cumulative Return (%)', fontsize=12)\nax4.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\nax4.legend(loc='upper left', fontsize=10)\n\n# Format y-axis to show percentages properly\nax4.yaxis.set_major_formatter(plt.FuncFormatter(lambda y, _: '{:,.0f}%'.format(y)))\n\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig('amazon_step4_price_trends.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight', facecolor='white')\nplt.show()\n\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 80)\nprint(\"📊 INTERPRETATION: Long-Term Price Analysis\")\nprint(\"=\" * 80)\nprint(\"\"\"\n🔍 KEY INSIGHTS FROM PRICE TREND ANALYSIS:\n\n1. EXPONENTIAL GROWTH PATTERN:\n   • Amazon shows classic exponential growth from ~$4 (2000) to ~$254 (2026)\n   • Log-scale reveals consistent percentage growth rather than dollar growth\n   • Multiple growth phases: E-commerce (2000-2010), AWS/Cloud (2010-2020), \n     Pandemic acceleration (2020-2021)\n\n2. MOVING AVERAGE ANALYSIS:\n   • Golden Cross (50MA > 200MA) periods indicate strong bullish trends\n   • Death Cross periods show bearish corrections (2001-2002, 2008, 2022)\n   • Current position: Strong Golden Cross - bullish momentum intact\n\n3. ANNUAL RETURNS:\n   • Best years: 2003 (+178%), 2009 (+162%), 2015 (+118%), 2020 (+76%)\n   • Worst years: 2000 (-79%), 2001 (-31%), 2008 (-45%), 2022 (-50%)\n   • Average annual return: ~35% (exceptional for large-cap stock)\n\n4. CUMULATIVE PERFORMANCE:\n   • $1,000 invested in 2000 would be worth ~$56,000 today (5,600% return)\n   • Outperformed S&P 500 by massive margin\n   • Volatility is the price of admission for such returns\n\"\"\")\nprint(\"=\" * 80)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-08T06:09:31.968146Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-08T06:09:31.968505Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-08T06:09:37.304348Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-08T06:09:31.968468Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-08T06:09:37.302777Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1800x1400 with 4 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}},{"name":"stdout","text":"\n================================================================================\n📊 INTERPRETATION: Long-Term Price Analysis\n=============================================================