nificant\n\n3. QUARTERLY PATTERNS:\n   • Q1: Often volatile (earnings season, guidance updates)\n   • Q2-Q3: Generally positive (summer growth)\n   • Q4: Strong performance (holiday season, year-end rally)\n\n4. VOLUME ANALYSIS:\n   • Volume spikes during earnings announcements and market stress\n   • 2000-2002: Extremely high volume (dot-com bubble burst)\n   • 2008: Volume surge during financial crisis\n   • 2020: COVID-19 volume spike\n   • Recent years: Lower volume (institutional holding increase)\n\n5. TRADING IMPLICATIONS:\n   • Seasonal effects are weak in AMZN - stock is driven by fundamentals\n   • Earnings announcements (Jan, Apr, Jul, Oct) create volatility\n   • No reliable seasonal arbitrage opportunities\n   • Volume precedes price movements - useful for confirmation\n\n================================================================================\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":7},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# =============================================================================\n# CELL 7: ADF TEST - STATIONARITY ANALYSIS\n# =============================================================================\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"\n\"\"\"\n## Step 5: Augmented Dickey-Fuller (ADF) Test for Stationarity 📊\n\nThe ADF test is crucial for time series analysis. It tests the null hypothesis \nthat a unit root is present in the time series (non-stationary).\n\n**Interpretation:**\n- p-value < 0.05: Reject null hypothesis → Series is STATIONARY\n- p-value ≥ 0.05: Fail to reject null → Series is NON-STATIONARY\n\nWe'll test:\n1. Raw closing prices (expected: non-stationary)\n2. First differences (expected: stationary)\n3. Log prices (expected: non-stationary)\n4. Log returns (expected: stationary)\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller\n\ndef perform_adf_test(series, title, alpha=0.05):\n    \"\"\"\n    Perform Augmented Dickey-Fuller test and return formatted results\n    \"\"\"\n    # Drop NaN values\n    series_clean = series.dropna()\n    \n    # Perform ADF test\n    result = adfuller(series_clean, autolag='AIC')\n    \n    # Extract results\n    adf_statistic = result[0]\n    p_value = result[1]\n    critical_values = result[4]\n    \n    # Determine stationarity\n    is_stationary = p_value < alpha\n    \n    # Create results dictionary\n    results = {\n        'title': title,\n        'adf_statistic': adf_statistic,\n        'p_value': p_value,\n        'critical_values': critical_values,\n        'is_stationary': is_stationary,\n        'series': series_clean\n    }\n    \n    return results\n\ndef print_adf_results(results):\n    \"\"\"Print formatted ADF test results\"\"\"\n    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n    print(f\"📊 ADF TEST RESULTS: {results['title']}\")\n    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n    print(f\"ADF Statistic:        {results['adf_statistic']:.6f}\")\n    print(f\"p-value:              {results['p_value']:.6f}\")\n    print(f\"\\nCritical Values:\")\n    for key, value in results['critical_values'].items():\n        print(f\"   {key}: {value:.6f}\")\n    \n    print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\")\n    if results['is_stationary']:\n        print(f\"✅ RESULT: STATIONARY (p < 0.05)\")\n        print(f\"   The series does NOT have a unit root.\")\n        print(f\"   Suitable for time series modeling without differencing.\")\n    else:\n        print(f\"❌ RESULT: NON-STATIONARY (p >= 0.05)\")\n        print(f\"   The series HAS a unit root.\")\n        print(f\"   Differencing required before modeling.\")\n    print(f\"{'='*60}\")\n    \n    return results['is_stationary']\n\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 80)\nprint(\"📊 STEP 5: AUGMENTED DICKEY-FULLER (ADF) STATIONARITY TESTS\")\nprint(\"=\" * 80)\n\n# Test 1: Raw Closing Prices\nprint(\"\\n🔍 TEST 1: Raw Closing Prices\")\nadf_price = perform_adf_test(df_features['Close'], \"Raw Closing Prices\")\nstationary_price = print_adf_results(adf_price)\n\n# Test 2: First Differences (Price Changes)\nprint(\"\\n🔍 TEST 2: First Differences (Price Changes)\")\nprice_diff = df_features['Close'].diff().dropna()\nadf_diff = perform_adf_test(price_diff, \"First Differences (Price Changes)\")\nstationary_diff = print_adf_results(adf_diff)\n\n# Test 3: Log Prices\nprint(\"\\n🔍 TEST 3: Logarithmic Prices\")\nlog_prices = np.log(df_features['Close'])\nadf_log = perform_adf_test(log_prices, \"Logarithmic Prices\")\nstationary_log = print_adf_results(adf_log)\n\n# Test 4: Log Returns (Percentage Changes)\nprint(\"\\n🔍 TEST 4: Log Returns (Continuously Compounded Returns)\")\nlog_returns = np.log(df_features['Close'] / df_features['Close'].shift(1)).dropna()\nadf_returns = perform_adf_test(log_returns, \"Log Returns\")\nstationary_returns = print_adf_results(adf_returns)\n\n# Test 5: First Differences of Log Prices (Same as Log Returns)\nprint(\"\\n🔍 TEST 5: First Differences of Log Prices\")\nlog_diff = np.log(df_features['Close']).diff().dropna()\nadf_log_diff = perform_adf_test(log_diff, \"First Differences of Log Prices\")\nstationary_log_diff = print_adf_results(adf_log_diff)\n\n# Summary table\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 80)\nprint(\"📋 ADF TEST SUMMARY TABLE\")\nprint(\"=\" * 80)\nprint(f\"{'Transformation':<40} {'ADF Stat':<12} {'p-value':<12} {'Stationary?':<12}\")\nprint(\"-\" * 80)\ntests = [\n    (\"Raw Closing Prices\", adf_price),\n    (\"First Differences\", adf_diff),\n    (\"Log Prices\", adf_log),\n    (\"Log Returns\", adf_returns),\n    (\"Diff of Log Prices\", adf_log_diff)\n]\n\nfor name, result in tests:\n    status = \"✅ YES\" if result['is_stationary'] else \"❌ NO\"\n    print(f\"{name:<40} {result['adf_statistic']:<12.4f} {result['p_value']:<12.6f} {status:<12}\")\n\nprint(\"=\" * 80)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-08T06:09:47.108033Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-08T06:09:47.108444Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-08T06:09:48.928708Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-08T06:09:47.108407Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-08T06:09:48.927879Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"\n================================================================================\n📊 STEP 5: AUGMENTED DICKEY-FULLER (ADF) STATIONARITY TESTS\n================================================================================\n\n🔍 TEST 1: Raw Closing Prices\n\n============================================================\n📊 ADF TEST RESULTS: Raw Closing Prices\n============================================================\nADF Statistic:        1.339250\np-value:              0.996820\n\nCritical Values:\n   1%: -3.431353\n   5%: -2.861983\n   10%: -2.567006\n\n============================================================\n❌ RESULT: NON-STATIONARY (p >= 0.05)\n   The series HAS a unit root.\n   Differencing required before modeling.\n============================================================\n\n🔍 TEST 2: First Differences (Price Changes)\n\n============================================================\n📊 ADF TEST RESULTS: First Differences (Price Changes)\n============================================================\nADF Statistic:        -13.506714\np-value:              0.000000\n\nCritical Values:\n   1%: -3.431353\n   5%: -2.861983\n   10%: -2.567006\n\n============================================================\n✅ RESULT: STATIONARY (p < 0.05)\n   The series does NOT have a unit root.\n   Suitable for time series modeling without differencing.\n============================================================\n\n🔍 TEST 3: Logarithmic Prices\n\n============================================================\n📊 ADF TEST RESULTS: Logarithmic Prices\n============================================================\nADF Statistic:        0.143666\np-value:              0.968919\n\nCritical Values:\n   1%: -3.431353\n   5%: -2.861983\n   10%: -2.567006\n\n============================================================\n❌ RESULT: NON-STATIONARY (p >= 0.05)\n   The series HAS a unit root.\n   Differencing required before modeling.\n=======